    <fr:title text="Lifted dcpos are positively generated › "><fr:link href="jms-0025.xml" title="Lifted dcpos are positively generated" addr="jms-0025" type="local">Lifted dcpos are positively generated</fr:link> › </fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u={\mathopen {}\left (\phi ,a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be an element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {L}{A}]]></fr:tex>. Note that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u]]></fr:tex> is equal to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigsqcup _{p:\phi }u]]></fr:tex>; as <fr:link href="jms-001N.xml" title="Positivity = definedness in a lifted dcpo" addr="jms-001N" type="local">definedness coincides with positivity</fr:link> in lifted dcpos, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi  = \mathsf {pos}\,u]]></fr:tex>, and so we are done.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
